comment: Eric's exploration of Apple's open-source packages was eye-opening! I had no idea about Swift Numerics and Swift Argument Parser.
Great overview of hidden gems in Apple's GitHub. The Swift Markdown examples were particularly useful.
Fantastic talk! Eric showed us tools I never knew existed. The Swift OpenAPI Generator will save me hours of work.
Very informative session on Apple's open-source ecosystem. The practical examples made it easy to understand.
Brilliant presentation! I'm excited to explore Swift Certificates and Swift Container Plugin for my projects.
Excellent deep dive into Apple's GitHub repositories. The Subprocess examples were particularly enlightening.
